                                <support><p><term>monument</term> <ref target="https://archwilio.org.uk/her/chi3/arch.php?lang=eng">Dyfed Archaeological Trust Historic Environment Record</ref>: <idno type="HER">1212</idno> Clydau, Clydey; St Clydai's Church</p>
                                    <material type="stone">Dolerite</material> <note>Comprised of <q>pyroxene-rich dolerite with sparse feldspar phenocrysts. Melanocratic, clearly defined pyroxene crystals and accessory minerals</q> (Edwards 2007, 314).</note>
